com.koverse.sdk.transform.spark

Interface SparkTransform

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    JavaSparkDataFrameTransform, JavaSparkSqlTransform, JavaSparkTransform
    Deprecated.

    @Deprecated
 @ThreadSafe
 @Immutable
public interface SparkTransform
    A Spark Koverse Transform. When installed, the following methods are executed in order to obtain information on how to execute the transform: getName(), getVersion(), and getParameters(). These are used to provide a UI to the user to configure the transform. When the transform is executed, the execute(com.koverse.sdk.transform.spark.SparkTransformContext) method is called. It is passed a SparkTransformContext to give it the information needed to run the spark transform.
